OL,7,FLouise Brown, representing Crisp, read
OL,8,Fa letter in which he said: "I wish to
OL,9,Fapologise unreservedly to all the
OL,10,Fpeople I have affected and for the
OL,11,Fupset and anger I have caused."
OL,13,FShe said the letter acknowledged that
OL,14,Fwhat he had written on X was
OL,15,F"derogatory, hurtful, distressing and
OL,16,Fdisrespectful" to fans of both West
OL,17,FBrom and Liverpool football clubs.
